#----
#neuron-data-1M  (this is a directory with the neuron data)
#vizu-src        (this is a directory with blender(2.79), python and slurm scripts)
#----

#cd to 'vizu-src' directory
$ cd vizu-src

#to run on this single workstation run the command:
[visu-src]$ ./run-script-v2.sh ../neuron-data-1M ../output-dir 0 100 1 1

That means that we pass data '../neuron-data-1M'
The output directory will be '../output-dir'
Start render frame 0
End render frame 100
Render Step = 1 
Render on one node = 1

#To run on the cluster:
1 open 'submit-job-array-v2.slurm' file
2 set number of nodes you planning to render on : #SBATCH --array=1-20 , (20 nodes)
3 set first render frame number = 0
4 set last render frame number = 10

#on the cluster, from login node run
[visu-src]$ sbatch submit-job-array-v2.slurm ../neuron-data-1M ../output-dir

#---------------------------
modify start-particles.blend in blender 2.79(or same version as installed on the clusted) so that all neurons are visible in render.
add camera animation if needed.
save start-particles.blend file after modifications.
restart render to see new results.
